- pull command :-
-  The pull command is used to download changes from a remote repository and immediately integrate them into your current local machine.
-  command :- git pull
-  the main perpose of this command is to avoid git cloning everytime.

- how it works:-
- the git pull command is actually a shorthand combination ot two distinct action.
1. git fetch : connect to your remote repository and downloads the newest commits without modifying your local working files.

2. git merge : immediately integrate those downloads commits into the local branch you are currently working on.
